The paper concerns the analysis of information leaks in security systems, which is a topic closely related to computer security (cs.CR). The paper proposes an algebraic approach for reasoning about information flow, which involves the manipulation of mathematical expressions and the study of their properties, suggesting that the paper may also belong to the logic in computer science (cs.LO) sub-category. The paper also deals with the specification and analysis of large systems, which may fall under the programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper applies the proposed algebraic approach to the Crowds Protocol, which is a topic related to cryptography (cs.CY).
